javadoc:
Class to represent an application's version information.

The version format is \d\.\d(\.\d)?(\-.+)?

Note: this class has a natural ordering that is inconsistent with equals (the tag part of the version is disregarded in the {@link #compareTo(ApplicationVersion)} method).

Examples:

  • 7.4
  • 7.4.1
  • 7.4.1-BETA

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Creates a new ApplicationVersion object from the given version string.

throws.comment:
if the version string failed to parse.  The 
   exception's message has more detailed information about why it failed.

methods.javadoc:
Gets the tag.

methods.name: getTag

return.comment: The tag.  Could be the empty string.

methods.name: parse
methods.comment: Parses the major, minor, patch, and tag components out of the given version string.

throws.comment:
if the version string failed to parse.  The 
   exception's message has more detailed information about why it failed.

methods.name: parse
methods.comment: Parses a version part string to an integer.

params.name: versionPartName
params.comment: The version part name (for error reporting).

throws.comment:
if the version part string failed to parse to a valid

return.comment: The version part string as an integer.
